A multifunction touchscreen display, digital 'infotainment system', hands free phone, air con and air suspension are also fitted as standard.

Having been in development for over 10 years, the new Metrocab has covered over 600,000 engineering test miles. 

London cabbies were invited to trial the new cab last year by registering online.

In April 2014 London Mayor Boris Johnson had a test drive in one of the new Metrocabs.  

