He said at the time: 'It's superb, an absolutely beautiful machine and a masterpiece of British engineering.

'I have just driven it and it's totally silent. It's the Rolls Royce of taxis and it will do 100mpg'.

So far a price tag has not yet been set, but Metrocab has announced there will be no price premium over the current black cab, which costs around £33,000.

The new Metrocab is driven by two independent brushless electric motors. 

A small petrol engine, coupled with a generator - the 'Range Extender' - is used to recharge the battery pack or provide power directly to the motors.

Plug-in charging is also achieved via any mains outlet when the taxi is off duty.

As pollution levels rise over major cities, governments are looking to more energy efficient, low emission, modes of transport.

A company spokesman said: 'The new Metrocab boasts an incredible environmental record, exceeding current standards.

'Metrocab can operate with zero emissions, giving it a range of well over 50 miles on its battery pack only.

